data.title: Woody Allen's new film: Cafe Society
data.meta_description: Check out the trailer for screen legend Woody Allen's new film, Cafe Society, starring Jesse Eisenberg, Kristen Stewart, Steve Carell.
data.text:
Filmed on location in New York and Los Angeles, Cafe Society is a romantic comedy about a young Bobby, played by Jesse Eisenberg, who arrives in Hollywood in the 1930s with dreams of a career in the film industry.

George Clooney and Julia Roberts star in 'Money Monster'

Watch the suspesnful new movie trailer: 'The Girl on the Train'

Eddy and Patsy are back in the new movie 'Absolutely Fabulous'

Instead, he finds himself both in love, and entranced by the cafe society that marked such a spirited age.

Kristen Stewart and Jesse Eisenberg star in Cafe Society

Woody Allen once again brings together a stellar cast including Jesse Eisenberg (who starred in Allen’s To Rome with Love), Kristen Stewart, Steve Carrell, Blake Lively, and Parker Posey (who starred in Allen’s Irrational Man).

Cafe Society opened the 69th Cannes International Film Festival in 2016

Cafe Society is in cinemas October 20.

The giveaway to win tickets to see the film has ended.
